es in which the survival efforts of farmers clash with the political imaginations and practices of the nation-state. The analysis shows that losing land represents more than being deprived of a material asset: it is nothing less than the extinction of ways of life.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-NC-ND 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-nd/4.0https://www.aup.nl/en/publish/open-access  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 4aAnthropology. 4aAsian Studies. 4aConflict and Peace. 4aEnvironment and Sustainability. 4aPolitics and Government. 4aSouth Asia. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / Political Economy.2bisacsh  aBangladesh, borderlands, nation-sate, indigenous, violence, agency, anthropology of life, land dispossession.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAmsterdam University Press Complete eBook-Package 2022z978311076709408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus PP Package 2022 Part 2z978311076700108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022 Englishz978311099389908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022z9783110994810oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Political Science 2022 Englishz978311099451308iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Political Science 2022z9783110994407oZDB-23-PLW0 cprintz978946372175240uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9789048553365?locatt=mode:legacyzOpen Access7040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9789048553365zOpen Access70423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9789048553365/original  a978-3-11-076700-1 DG Plus PP Package 2022 Part 2b2022  a978-3-11-076709-4 Amsterdam University Press Complete eBook-Package 2022b2022  a978-3-11-099389-9 EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022